text: Whitman is an unincorporated community in Walla Walla County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Whitman was established in 1870, and remained in operation until 1875. The community was named after Marcus Whitman, a missionary who was killed by Indians. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Walla Walla County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Whitman, Washington
